title: Yahoo Lifestyle
text: Thinking for yourself sets you apart from the crowd. Although this kind of independence may place a few extra responsibilities onto your shoulders, the confidence it inspires makes the burden a lighter load to bear. While a few folks might be a little jealous, most people truly admire your ability to set your own course and follow it without distraction. In fact, others might even see you as a role model, so be mindful of your actions. Joe DiMaggio said, A person always doing his or her best becomes a natural leader, just by example.
